WEBVTT

00:00:02.922 --> 00:00:06.428
[RINKO]
Hey, uh, Takeo, everything
got so exciting on New Year's

00:00:06.528 --> 00:00:10.771
that I totally forgot to
give something to your mom.

00:00:10.871 --> 00:00:13.743
[TAKEO]
Oh! Thanks, Ms. Yamato!

00:00:15.379 --> 00:00:19.321
[RINKO]
I must admit I was a little
out of it that day.

00:00:19.989 --> 00:00:21.391
<i>Yeah. Same here.</i>

00:00:21.491 --> 00:00:22.861
<i>I love her!</i>

00:00:22.962 --> 00:00:24.364
Hey, you know what?
Huh?

00:00:24.464 --> 00:00:26.268
You should bring it
to my place.

00:00:26.368 --> 00:00:29.407
It'd make mom super happy if you
gave it to her personally.

00:00:29.507 --> 00:00:30.677
Mm-hmm!

00:00:30.777 --> 00:00:32.915
(Aggressive grunts)

00:00:33.015 --> 00:00:34.986
What are you doing?!

00:00:35.086 --> 00:00:36.154
Cleaning the house.

00:00:36.255 --> 00:00:37.591
You need to rest!

00:00:37.691 --> 00:00:39.795
I did this when I was carrying
you around, too.

00:00:39.895 --> 00:00:40.831
AHHH!

00:00:40.931 --> 00:00:41.899
[YURIKO]
Oh, hello dear.

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:42.835
Good to see you!

00:00:42.935 --> 00:00:44.271
Hello, ma'am!

00:00:44.371 --> 00:00:46.275
Well, I'm off to the
store to get some rice.

00:00:46.375 --> 00:00:48.045
Hang on! How much
are you getting?

00:00:48.145 --> 00:00:48.980
22 pounds.

00:00:49.080 --> 00:00:50.016
Then I'll go!

00:00:50.116 --> 00:00:51.218
Oh great...

00:00:51.318 --> 00:00:53.556
Then you can get
everything else too.

00:00:53.657 --> 00:00:56.094
♪Opening song♪

00:02:26.475 --> 00:02:28.379
[YURIKO]
The men in this
house are the worst.

00:02:28.479 --> 00:02:30.383
They are such
worry warts.

00:02:30.483 --> 00:02:31.986
Aw, they just care about you.

00:02:32.086 --> 00:02:33.222
Ohh...

00:02:33.322 --> 00:02:34.792
They're overprotective.

00:02:34.892 --> 00:02:36.863
I should show them
my last maternity checkup.

00:02:36.963 --> 00:02:39.735
I am as strong as a bull
with no complications.

00:02:39.835 --> 00:02:44.310
I really hope that someday
I can be as strong of
a mother as you are.

00:02:44.411 --> 00:02:47.517
I'm sure you will.
Men are such wimps!

00:02:47.618 --> 00:02:50.089
It's us women who have
to be the tough ones!

00:02:50.189 --> 00:02:52.393
Huh? But Takeo's
pretty tough.

00:02:52.493 --> 00:02:54.497
Oh no, not like that.

00:02:54.598 --> 00:02:56.736
Back when that boy
was about five years old,

00:02:56.836 --> 00:02:59.340
we were waiting for the bus
to take him to kindergarten...

00:02:59.441 --> 00:03:01.946
and that knucklehead jumped
right out in the street.

00:03:02.046 --> 00:03:04.919
Well I was able to jump in
and knock him out of the way,

00:03:05.019 --> 00:03:06.656
but I scraped my
arm pretty good.

00:03:06.756 --> 00:03:10.997
I got this and bled all over
the place! And then, Take...

00:03:11.098 --> 00:03:12.935
Please, Mom, don't die!

00:03:13.035 --> 00:03:16.341
[YURIKO]
All this from a boy who got
cuts and bruises every day

00:03:16.441 --> 00:03:18.178
and never made a fuss about it.

00:03:18.278 --> 00:03:22.220
That's sweet...
Sounds like he's cared about
you ever since he was little.

00:03:22.320 --> 00:03:23.890
And he's always been a wimp.

00:03:23.990 --> 00:03:26.929
It sounds to me like Takeo
just loves his mother, right?

00:03:27.029 --> 00:03:28.833
Yeah, he's a mama's boy.

00:03:29.935 --> 00:03:33.408
Men can be weak in some
rather unusual ways.

00:03:33.509 --> 00:03:35.680
So please, be there for him.

00:03:35.781 --> 00:03:36.749
Alright.

00:03:36.849 --> 00:03:38.285
[YURIKO]
And when he was
born, there was

00:03:38.385 --> 00:03:39.989
thunderous applause from
the delivery room.

00:03:40.089 --> 00:03:41.859
[RINKO] No way!
[TAKEO] <i>They sound like</i>
<i>they're having fun.</i>

00:03:41.959 --> 00:03:44.330
So when I went in for
his one-month checkup,

00:03:44.430 --> 00:03:46.569
the nurse raised him
up over her head...

00:03:46.669 --> 00:03:48.840
"The Yokozuna has arrived!"

00:03:48.940 --> 00:03:50.509
Just like The Lion King!

00:03:50.610 --> 00:03:52.346
Yeah, right.
Wait, the what?

00:03:52.446 --> 00:03:54.017
Oh, hey there, Takeo!

00:03:54.117 --> 00:03:55.554
That was fast.
[TAKEO] Yeah.

00:03:55.654 --> 00:03:58.025
Goodness gracious!
How much rice did you buy?

00:03:58.125 --> 00:03:59.461
I just stocked us up.

00:03:59.562 --> 00:04:02.701
Take, did you use all the
money I had in my wallet?

00:04:02.801 --> 00:04:03.903
Good grief!

00:04:04.003 --> 00:04:07.009
Well, I'm off to the
hospital for my checkup.

00:04:07.109 --> 00:04:09.047
Huh? Okay. Be careful!

00:04:09.147 --> 00:04:10.182
Oh, um...!

00:04:10.282 --> 00:04:13.656
Huh?
[RINKO] Take this.

00:04:13.756 --> 00:04:17.965
Oh my, what's this?
Thank you so much, sweetie.

00:04:18.065 --> 00:04:19.267
Have a good checkup!

00:04:19.367 --> 00:04:20.670
Alrighty!

00:04:20.770 --> 00:04:23.108
Your mom said you were
nine and a half pounds

00:04:23.208 --> 00:04:24.377
when you were born.

00:04:24.477 --> 00:04:26.682
Yeah, I was a big boy.

00:04:26.782 --> 00:04:30.055
Well, I was a preemie
and only weighed four pounds.

00:04:30.156 --> 00:04:34.698
I ended up spending a long
time in an incubator before
they would let me out.

00:04:34.798 --> 00:04:39.440
I was so small that
I couldn't go home with
my mom from the hospital.

00:04:39.541 --> 00:04:41.411
But I'm super healthy now!

00:04:41.511 --> 00:04:43.248
That's right.
You're a beast!

00:04:43.348 --> 00:04:44.384
Yeah!

00:04:44.484 --> 00:04:46.221
I can't wait to
see the baby!

00:04:46.321 --> 00:04:47.824
Yeah!

00:04:50.162 --> 00:04:51.097
(Pained breath)

00:04:51.198 --> 00:04:52.333
Hi there.

00:04:52.433 --> 00:04:53.836
Is it almost time?

00:04:53.937 --> 00:04:56.609
Yeah. I'm anemic again,
so they're watching me.

00:04:56.709 --> 00:04:59.180
[SON]
Mama! Watch me! Watch me!
Whooo! Whooo!

00:04:59.280 --> 00:05:00.951
Honey. Please calm down.

00:05:01.051 --> 00:05:02.186
Is that the brother?

00:05:02.286 --> 00:05:04.057
Oh, yeah.

00:05:04.157 --> 00:05:07.530
Initially I had hoped
to have the second
closer to the first,

00:05:07.631 --> 00:05:10.369
but they ended up being
a few years apart.

00:05:10.469 --> 00:05:13.475
Well I'm glad you were
able to have another one.

00:05:14.410 --> 00:05:16.749
Your big brother's
waiting for you!

00:05:16.849 --> 00:05:18.485
Huh?

00:05:19.220 --> 00:05:21.057
It won't be long.

00:05:21.157 --> 00:05:23.730
(Receding footsteps)

00:05:23.830 --> 00:05:25.499
There we go.

00:05:25.600 --> 00:05:27.838
Mom, you shouldn't
be doing that!

00:05:27.938 --> 00:05:30.409
How did everything
go at the hospital?

00:05:30.509 --> 00:05:32.113
It was a piece of cake.

00:05:32.213 --> 00:05:34.017
That's good.

00:05:34.117 --> 00:05:36.321
When Ms. Yamato
was a baby,

00:05:36.421 --> 00:05:38.960
she only weighed like
half of what I did.

00:05:39.060 --> 00:05:43.235
She couldn't even go home from
the hospital with her mom.

00:05:43.335 --> 00:05:45.306
Oh yeah?

00:05:45.406 --> 00:05:48.211
Take, now you must
understand...

00:05:48.312 --> 00:05:52.153
not every baby is born healthy,
or gets to live a normal life.

00:05:52.253 --> 00:05:53.422
(Door opens)

00:05:53.522 --> 00:05:55.192
Hey there, Honey.

00:05:55.292 --> 00:05:57.496
You rest up, I'm gonna
clean the bathtub.

00:05:57.598 --> 00:05:58.866
(Phone jingle)

00:05:58.967 --> 00:06:00.202
AHHHHH!

00:06:00.302 --> 00:06:02.774
[TAKEO]
<i>What an angel!</i>

00:06:02.874 --> 00:06:09.153
<i>She was so tiny... I'm glad</i>
<i>she grew up like she did.</i>

00:06:09.254 --> 00:06:11.993
<i>I was born bigger than most,</i>

00:06:12.093 --> 00:06:15.432
<i>and I never really got sick</i>
<i>or anything like that.</i>

00:06:15.532 --> 00:06:19.507
<i>I guess I never thought</i>
<i>about it before.</i>

00:06:21.311 --> 00:06:25.654
<i>But it's not something that</i>
<i>should be taken for granted.</i>

00:06:25.754 --> 00:06:27.557
Hey, lemme take
that for you.

00:06:27.658 --> 00:06:32.199
Not you, too! I swear,
you all worry too much.

00:06:32.300 --> 00:06:34.370
I'm not as bad as Takeo.

00:06:34.470 --> 00:06:36.676
He has a good friend
in you, ya know.

00:06:36.776 --> 00:06:38.846
And the cutest little
girlfriend.

00:06:38.946 --> 00:06:42.286
It's a rare thing.
He's a very lucky boy.

00:06:42.386 --> 00:06:44.123
Well it's because
he's a good guy.

00:06:44.223 --> 00:06:48.733
Whenever I look at him,
I still see a little baby boy.

00:06:50.235 --> 00:06:55.112
I hope this one will end up with
friends as good as Take has.

00:06:55.212 --> 00:06:57.516
[TAKEO]
Thanks for giving my
mom that lucky charm.

00:06:57.617 --> 00:07:00.824
Mom totally loves it.
She takes it with her
everywhere in her purse.

00:07:00.924 --> 00:07:04.230
Really? That makes
me so happy!

00:07:05.600 --> 00:07:07.971
I hope we meet
the baby soon.

00:07:08.940 --> 00:07:10.275
<i>Yeah. Me too.</i>

00:07:10.376 --> 00:07:13.883
Oh! I want to see a picture of
you at a hundred days old, too.

00:07:13.983 --> 00:07:14.985
Okay.

00:07:15.085 --> 00:07:16.555
[TAKEO]
I'm home!

00:07:16.656 --> 00:07:18.793
What are you doing?!
AHHH!

00:07:18.893 --> 00:07:20.295
Oh, hi, son.

00:07:20.396 --> 00:07:21.799
This position is good for me.

00:07:21.899 --> 00:07:24.672
They say that it
will ease the delivery.

00:07:24.772 --> 00:07:26.141
<i>That may be the case,</i>

00:07:26.241 --> 00:07:28.746
<i>but it still looks like</i>
<i>you're working too hard.</i>

00:07:28.846 --> 00:07:30.850
(Pained groan)
AHH!

00:07:30.950 --> 00:07:31.786
Mom?!

00:07:31.886 --> 00:07:32.988
Well...

00:07:33.088 --> 00:07:35.627
looks like the baby really
knows how to kick...

00:07:35.727 --> 00:07:38.065
We've got ourselves a
healthy one on the way.

00:07:38.165 --> 00:07:39.333
[YUTAKA]
I'm home.

00:07:39.434 --> 00:07:40.904
Alrighty! Time to clean the-

00:07:41.004 --> 00:07:41.972
AAUGH!

00:07:42.073 --> 00:07:43.375
(THUD)

00:07:43.475 --> 00:07:45.914
<i>I was huge.</i>
<i>(Shudder sound)</i>

00:07:47.116 --> 00:07:48.452
(Jingle)

00:07:48.553 --> 00:07:51.692
[TAKEO]
<i>But pretty cute, honestly.</i>

00:07:54.598 --> 00:07:55.900
[YURIKO]
Okay. I'm heading out.

00:07:56.000 --> 00:07:57.403
[TAKEO]
Wait, where are you going?!

00:07:57.503 --> 00:07:59.107
I'm just going for a walk.

00:07:59.207 --> 00:08:01.544
It's good for the baby's health
for me to go on frequent walks.

00:08:01.645 --> 00:08:04.317
Then I'm gonna come
with you, 'kay?
Me, too!

00:08:04.417 --> 00:08:06.989
I am not dragging
you two ninnies around
the block with me!

00:08:07.089 --> 00:08:08.525
You'll slow me down!

00:08:08.626 --> 00:08:10.028
[YURIKO]
I'm leaving!
(Door closes)

00:08:10.129 --> 00:08:11.131
Hmm...

00:08:11.231 --> 00:08:13.068
<i>I'm worried.</i>

00:08:15.072 --> 00:08:16.842
Takeo.
Huh?

00:08:16.942 --> 00:08:19.280
Son, have I ever told
you the reason why

00:08:19.380 --> 00:08:20.784
I fell in love
with your mother?

00:08:20.884 --> 00:08:22.420
I don't think so.

00:08:22.520 --> 00:08:24.558
Well, your mother and I
both started working

00:08:24.658 --> 00:08:26.929
for the same company
at the same time...

00:08:27.029 --> 00:08:31.037
And your mother had
this presence about her.
She seemed so positive.

00:08:31.137 --> 00:08:34.310
She was by far the hardest
worker in the entire office.

00:08:34.410 --> 00:08:38.285
All her supervisors loved
her, and she could always
be counted on.

00:08:38.385 --> 00:08:39.520
Oh wow.

00:08:39.621 --> 00:08:41.391
And that year,
at the company party...

00:08:41.491 --> 00:08:44.497
[WORKER]
Ms. Takenaka, could you do me
a favor and pass this for me?

00:08:44.598 --> 00:08:46.234
Sure thing.

00:08:47.269 --> 00:08:49.073
Careful now. It's hot.

00:08:49.173 --> 00:08:50.509
Mm-hmm...

00:08:50.610 --> 00:08:52.179
AHH!
OH!

00:08:52.279 --> 00:08:53.548
AH!

00:08:53.649 --> 00:08:55.085
(Teapot clatters)

00:08:55.185 --> 00:08:56.822
[COWORKER]
Yuriko, your hand!

00:08:56.922 --> 00:08:59.928
I'm okay. You didn't get
burnt, did you, dear?

00:09:00.028 --> 00:09:01.999
No. I'm fine.
I'll rinse this off.

00:09:02.099 --> 00:09:05.005
I'm wearing lots of layers.
Don't worry about me.

00:09:05.105 --> 00:09:07.510
[YUTAKA]
You want me to
get you some ice?

00:09:07.611 --> 00:09:11.284
Huh? Oh, no...
I'm fine. I'll be all right.

00:09:11.384 --> 00:09:14.691
[YURIKO]
It's just when I see a cute
little thing like that,

00:09:14.792 --> 00:09:16.896
I feel the need
to protect them.

00:09:16.996 --> 00:09:21.337
[YUTAKA]
<i>At that moment, for the</i>
<i>first time in my life...</i>

00:09:21.437 --> 00:09:23.041
(Amazed gasp)

00:09:23.141 --> 00:09:25.312
<i>I knew I must be</i>
<i>with this woman</i>

00:09:25.412 --> 00:09:28.986
<i>and face the towering</i>
<i>waves of life with her!</i>

00:09:29.086 --> 00:09:30.790
[YUTAKA]
Would you like to
go golfing with me?

00:09:30.890 --> 00:09:33.295
I see your core
is rock solid.

00:09:33.395 --> 00:09:35.667
Shall we go on
a scenic drive?

00:09:37.036 --> 00:09:39.808
I want to be your
protector, Ms. Takenaka!

00:09:39.908 --> 00:09:42.714
(Ship horn blows)

00:09:42.814 --> 00:09:44.718
But your mother is so strong

00:09:44.818 --> 00:09:48.291
that I've never really
needed to do much protecting.

00:09:49.895 --> 00:09:52.667
Hi, Mrs. Goda.
Oh, hello there.

00:09:52.767 --> 00:09:55.072
I guess you have a checkup
tomorrow, too, don't you?

00:09:55.172 --> 00:09:58.044
Yes, I do. Both of us are
getting pretty close.

00:09:58.144 --> 00:10:00.215
Yeah. I'll see
you tomorrow then.

00:10:01.117 --> 00:10:02.386
Ah...

00:10:02.486 --> 00:10:03.255
Uh!

00:10:03.355 --> 00:10:04.390
Huh?

00:10:04.490 --> 00:10:05.960
HUH?!

00:10:07.329 --> 00:10:09.601
(Both grunt)

00:10:09.701 --> 00:10:11.204
(Pained grunt)

00:10:11.304 --> 00:10:12.974
Uh... Ah?

00:10:13.074 --> 00:10:15.914
Mrs. Goda! Oh my god!
Are you all right?

00:10:16.014 --> 00:10:18.451
I'm perfectly fine!
How about you?

00:10:18.553 --> 00:10:20.790
Um... well, I think
I'm okay.

00:10:20.890 --> 00:10:22.594
You need to be careful.

00:10:22.694 --> 00:10:24.363
I will. Thank you so much.

00:10:24.463 --> 00:10:25.600
[SON]
Bye-bye!

00:10:25.700 --> 00:10:27.269
(Sigh)

00:10:27.369 --> 00:10:29.908
[SUNA]
So you guys don't know
if it's a boy or a girl yet?

00:10:30.008 --> 00:10:32.781
Nope. What do you
think it'll be?

00:10:32.881 --> 00:10:35.085
I dunno. I've no idea.

00:10:35.185 --> 00:10:38.693
But I can't really imagine it
turning out to be a girl...

00:10:38.793 --> 00:10:41.632
Heh! In fact I can only see
it with a face like yours.

00:10:41.732 --> 00:10:43.268
(Laughs)
What's so funny
about that?

00:10:43.368 --> 00:10:46.976
<i>A little brother</i>
<i>or a little sister...</i>

00:10:47.076 --> 00:10:50.249
[TAKEO]
Guess you're right.
I can only see my face too.

00:10:50.349 --> 00:10:52.052
(Suna continues laughing)

00:10:52.152 --> 00:10:54.257
Hey! It's not that funny!

00:10:54.357 --> 00:10:56.060
I'm home!

00:10:56.160 --> 00:10:57.062
AHH?!

00:10:57.162 --> 00:10:58.031
(Pained groans)

00:10:58.131 --> 00:10:59.868
[TAKEO]
What's wrong? What happened?

00:10:59.968 --> 00:11:01.772
Did the baby start
kicking again?

00:11:01.872 --> 00:11:04.945
Uh, Take... you
need to get a taxi.

00:11:05.045 --> 00:11:07.316
Mom needs to get
to the hospital.

00:11:07.416 --> 00:11:08.418
Ugghh...

00:11:08.518 --> 00:11:11.692
(Takeo grunting)

00:11:12.293 --> 00:11:13.763
[TAKEO]
What the...?

00:11:13.863 --> 00:11:16.200
(Heavy breathing)

00:11:16.301 --> 00:11:18.706
Where the heck are
all the taxis?!

00:11:18.806 --> 00:11:21.210
(Doors open)
Ahh...

00:11:21.311 --> 00:11:25.319
Takeo, what's going on?
Is everything okay?

00:11:25.419 --> 00:11:28.893
Uh! It's Mom!

00:11:34.070 --> 00:11:37.376
[TAKEO]
<i>I guess I could've</i>
<i>just used the phone.</i>

00:11:37.476 --> 00:11:38.545
(Groans)

00:11:38.646 --> 00:11:39.915
[TAKEO]
<i>Dad's at work.</i>

00:11:40.015 --> 00:11:41.719
<i>I have got to</i>
<i>hold it together.</i>

00:11:41.819 --> 00:11:42.854
[DRIVER]
Sir, where to?

00:11:42.954 --> 00:11:44.691
It is on me.
(Door opens)

00:11:44.791 --> 00:11:46.795
Sir?
<i>But what should I do?</i>
<i>What should-</i>

00:11:46.895 --> 00:11:49.300
[SUNA]
Head to Shisuta
General Hospital.

00:11:49.935 --> 00:11:51.170
I'll go with you.

00:11:51.271 --> 00:11:52.774
[TAKEO]
<i>Suna...</i>

00:11:53.743 --> 00:11:55.245
I'll be fine.

00:11:55.345 --> 00:11:58.451
Take, I'm sorry, but I forgot
my wallet back at the house.

00:11:58.551 --> 00:12:00.155
I'll go get it!

00:12:00.255 --> 00:12:02.827
Don't worry about it.
I took care of the cab.

00:12:02.927 --> 00:12:05.633
Oh, Suna, you are
so responsible.

00:12:05.733 --> 00:12:07.369
Mom! Where did you
leave your wallet?

00:12:07.469 --> 00:12:08.606
On top of the dresser.

00:12:08.706 --> 00:12:09.941
I'll be right back!

00:12:10.042 --> 00:12:12.814
That boy really needs
to calm down a bit.

00:12:12.914 --> 00:12:15.052
Yeah. But that's
kind of his charm.

00:12:15.152 --> 00:12:19.527
You're too nice to Take.
Both you and his girlfriend.

00:12:19.628 --> 00:12:21.598
[TAKEO]
Where's Mom?!

00:12:21.699 --> 00:12:23.335
(Heavy breathing)

00:12:23.435 --> 00:12:24.671
She's with the doctor.

00:12:24.771 --> 00:12:27.276
Calm down! Suna, get
a hold of yourself!

00:12:27.376 --> 00:12:29.380
You're the one who
needs to calm down.

00:12:29.480 --> 00:12:31.050
Sorry.

00:12:31.150 --> 00:12:32.219
It's cool.

00:12:32.319 --> 00:12:34.390
She's always been
healthy, hasn't she?

00:12:34.490 --> 00:12:35.893
Yeah.

00:12:35.994 --> 00:12:39.166
It's the first time
I've seen her like
that, you know?

00:12:39.266 --> 00:12:40.369
Yeah.

00:12:41.437 --> 00:12:42.674
Sorry, man.

00:12:42.774 --> 00:12:43.709
Mm-hmm.

00:12:43.809 --> 00:12:45.278
(Doors open)
Huh?

00:12:45.379 --> 00:12:48.118
Oh, Take... were you able
to find my wallet?

00:12:48.218 --> 00:12:51.224
Yeah! Are you and
the baby alright?

00:12:51.324 --> 00:12:52.594
YEP!

00:12:52.694 --> 00:12:54.530
But I'm going to
stay at the hospital.

00:12:54.631 --> 00:12:56.602
<i>"Stay at the hospital"?</i>

00:12:56.702 --> 00:13:00.710
There are some things you'll
need to take care of,
so write this down.

00:13:00.810 --> 00:13:01.979
I got it.

00:13:02.079 --> 00:13:03.849
There's a bag I packed
up for the hospital.

00:13:03.949 --> 00:13:05.653
It's in my room,
I need you to bring it here.

00:13:05.753 --> 00:13:08.324
Then, you need to wash
the dishes, and keep
up with the laundry.

00:13:08.425 --> 00:13:11.665
Also, tomorrow is heavy trash
day, so take it to the curb...

00:13:11.765 --> 00:13:14.771
(Receding)
As far as your father,
I'll call him myself.

00:13:14.871 --> 00:13:16.608
Take!
OH!

00:13:16.709 --> 00:13:19.915
I'm fine, okay?
Try not to worry.

00:13:21.184 --> 00:13:23.021
[NURSE]
I'll show you to
your room, ma'am.

00:13:23.121 --> 00:13:25.258
Please take
care of my mom!
AHH!

00:13:25.359 --> 00:13:26.494
O-of course!

00:13:26.595 --> 00:13:27.964
(Grunting)

00:13:28.064 --> 00:13:29.634
[TAKEO]
Was there a break-in?!

00:13:29.735 --> 00:13:31.003
Oh, wait. No, that was me.

00:13:31.104 --> 00:13:32.707
Here's the bag. I'm out!

00:13:32.807 --> 00:13:35.412
Yessir. Mrs. Goda
is in Room 203.
Thanks!

00:13:35.512 --> 00:13:37.751
Oh, your wife is
currently getting examined.

00:13:37.851 --> 00:13:39.520
I'll take her
luggage for you.

00:13:39.621 --> 00:13:42.560
Thanks! Please take
good care of her!
Hm!

00:13:43.996 --> 00:13:47.369
<i>Suna... Did he go home?</i>

00:13:48.806 --> 00:13:51.645
<i>I have to pull myself together.</i>

00:13:51.745 --> 00:13:52.647
[RINKO]
Takeo!

00:13:52.747 --> 00:13:54.450
(Heavy breaths)

00:13:54.550 --> 00:13:57.757
[RINKO]
Suna called me and said that
your mom was in the hospital.

00:13:57.857 --> 00:13:58.726
Is that right?

00:13:58.826 --> 00:14:00.630
(Light laugh)

00:14:00.730 --> 00:14:02.366
Can I use your kitchen?

00:14:02.466 --> 00:14:05.773
I'll make some curry!
I already went to the store!

00:14:05.873 --> 00:14:07.610
Hey there, Takeo. How are ya?

00:14:07.710 --> 00:14:10.048
[SUNA AND RINKO]
Excuse us!

00:14:10.148 --> 00:14:12.286
Uh, Takeo.
You didn't peel them.

00:14:12.386 --> 00:14:13.923
(Giggle)

00:14:15.560 --> 00:14:17.096
[SUNA]
Dude, that's bleach.

00:14:17.196 --> 00:14:20.570
It not too sweet?
My curry is kinda sweet.

00:14:22.807 --> 00:14:25.078
Oh, no, you don't
have to walk me.

00:14:25.178 --> 00:14:27.516
You should really stay
here at home, Takeo.

00:14:27.617 --> 00:14:28.619
Okay.

00:14:30.122 --> 00:14:33.461
If you need any help.
Call and I'll be right over.

00:14:33.562 --> 00:14:35.800
Okay. Thanks.

00:14:35.900 --> 00:14:41.812
(Numerous TV commercials)

00:14:41.912 --> 00:14:43.682
(Door opens)
[YUTAKA]
I'm home!

00:14:43.783 --> 00:14:45.252
Huh?!

00:14:47.089 --> 00:14:49.059
I see there's a pot
of curry here.

00:14:49.160 --> 00:14:51.063
Did you make this, Takeo?

00:14:51.164 --> 00:14:53.836
Nah, Ms. Yamato
made it for us.

00:14:53.936 --> 00:14:55.740
Well, alrighty.

00:14:55.840 --> 00:14:57.610
You stopped by
the hospital, right?

00:14:57.710 --> 00:14:58.979
How was Mom?
How's the baby?

00:14:59.079 --> 00:15:00.883
Any news?!
What's going on?!

00:15:00.983 --> 00:15:03.021
Everything's going
to be fine, son.

00:15:03.121 --> 00:15:04.523
Don't you worry about it.

00:15:04.624 --> 00:15:07.429
Drop by the hospital on your way
home from school tomorrow.

00:15:07.529 --> 00:15:08.465
Okay.

00:15:08.566 --> 00:15:10.068
Well, it was a good
thing you were here

00:15:10.168 --> 00:15:11.672
at the house today.

00:15:11.772 --> 00:15:14.009
[YURIKO]
There's another pregnant woman
who'll be giving birth

00:15:14.109 --> 00:15:15.947
around the same time as I will.

00:15:16.047 --> 00:15:17.449
She was walking up
the stairs and tripped,

00:15:17.549 --> 00:15:19.353
and when I stepped
in to catch her,

00:15:19.453 --> 00:15:21.390
I think I hurt
something in my stomach.

00:15:21.491 --> 00:15:24.330
I just did it
without even thinking.

00:15:24.430 --> 00:15:28.572
I hope I didn't do something to
upset our baby and make it mad.

00:15:28.672 --> 00:15:30.308
I'm sure it's fine.

00:15:30.408 --> 00:15:34.718
I know that you were just
trying to help someone who
was in trouble.

00:15:34.818 --> 00:15:37.757
[TEACHER]
Okay, next up, turn to
page 53 in your textbooks...

00:15:37.857 --> 00:15:39.226
(Intense groan)

00:15:39.326 --> 00:15:40.596
Now, who wants to volunteer
to read the first section?

00:15:40.696 --> 00:15:43.434
BRBRBRBR!
<i>I have to pull</i>
<i>myself together!</i>

00:15:43.535 --> 00:15:46.207
(Schoolbell rings)
(Grunting)

00:15:46.307 --> 00:15:47.977
Huh?

00:15:48.979 --> 00:15:50.115
(Phone jingle)

00:15:50.215 --> 00:15:52.219
[TAKEO]
Is it the hospital?!

00:15:52.854 --> 00:15:53.956
<i>Ms. Yamato...</i>

00:15:54.056 --> 00:15:55.693
(Phone jingles)

00:15:55.793 --> 00:15:59.266
(Heavy breathing)

00:16:01.337 --> 00:16:03.174
(Jingle)

00:16:03.274 --> 00:16:05.746
<i>Pull it together, man!</i>

00:16:05.846 --> 00:16:07.049
No running, please.

00:16:07.149 --> 00:16:09.453
Erk! I'm sorry.

00:16:09.554 --> 00:16:11.524
Hello! Mom?!

00:16:11.625 --> 00:16:13.361
(Pained groans)

00:16:13.461 --> 00:16:14.731
Hello, Take.

00:16:14.831 --> 00:16:18.171
Oh, would you please stop
looking so worried all the time?

00:16:18.271 --> 00:16:20.442
[TAKEO]
What are you doing?
Don't sit up!

00:16:20.542 --> 00:16:23.314
Take, I am not on the
brink of death, okay?

00:16:23.414 --> 00:16:24.951
Relax. I'm going to be fine.

00:16:25.051 --> 00:16:28.191
[TAKEO]
Is there anything
I can do for you?

00:16:28.291 --> 00:16:30.897
Oh, well, some water
would be nice.

00:16:30.997 --> 00:16:32.667
(Loud clank)

00:16:32.767 --> 00:16:36.274
<i>Was she looking pale?</i>
<i>I think she looked pale.</i>

00:16:36.374 --> 00:16:38.812
<i>And she was sweating...</i>

00:16:38.913 --> 00:16:40.816
<i>I don't understand</i>
<i>much about this,</i>

00:16:40.917 --> 00:16:44.858
<i>but a human is about to come</i>
<i>out from another human.</i>

00:16:44.958 --> 00:16:48.164
<i>And that's kind of a big deal.</i>

00:16:48.264 --> 00:16:51.772
<i>Isn't there anything</i>
<i>I can do to help?</i>

00:16:54.476 --> 00:16:55.312
Huh?

00:16:55.412 --> 00:16:58.484
Hey, Takeo!
How's your mom doing?

00:16:59.153 --> 00:17:00.422
<i>Ms. Yamato...</i>

00:17:00.522 --> 00:17:01.992
(Giggle)

00:17:02.092 --> 00:17:04.998
It's all right!
I'm here by your side!

00:17:05.098 --> 00:17:07.469
Your mom's room.
Second floor, right?

00:17:07.570 --> 00:17:08.706
[TAKEO]
Yeah.

00:17:08.806 --> 00:17:11.077
<i>I'm being so pathetic.</i>

00:17:11.177 --> 00:17:12.914
<i>I'm not a little kid anymore.</i>

00:17:13.014 --> 00:17:16.520
<i>Right now, my mom and the baby</i>
<i>are acting more brave than me.</i>

00:17:16.622 --> 00:17:19.493
Right! It's time to
go cheer up my mom!

00:17:19.594 --> 00:17:22.532
Mom! Suna and Ms. Yamato
came to see you-

00:17:22.634 --> 00:17:23.702
AGHH!

00:17:23.802 --> 00:17:25.272
(Intense groan)

00:17:25.372 --> 00:17:27.777
[YURIKO]
Take, hit the
nurse-call button!

00:17:27.877 --> 00:17:29.513
I've been in labor
for awhile now.

00:17:29.614 --> 00:17:32.219
I don't think I can walk!
UGHHH!

00:17:32.319 --> 00:17:34.858
Okay! I'm on it! AAAHH!

00:17:34.958 --> 00:17:36.527
[SUNA]
Dude, it's over here.
(Beep)

00:17:36.628 --> 00:17:38.131
[NURSE]
Yes. How can I help you?

00:17:38.231 --> 00:17:40.035
[TAKEO]
The baby's coming! Help us!

00:17:40.135 --> 00:17:41.170
Okay, Mom!
It's gonna be all right!

00:17:41.270 --> 00:17:42.339
She says she can't walk.

00:17:42.439 --> 00:17:43.642
I think we'll need a wheelchair.

00:17:43.742 --> 00:17:45.646
Can you hear me in there?!
It's your brother!

00:17:45.746 --> 00:17:47.717
I need you to get outta
there safe and sound!

00:17:47.817 --> 00:17:49.587
I'll be waiting for you!

00:17:49.688 --> 00:17:51.357
(Beep)
(Groan)

00:17:51.457 --> 00:17:52.794
[NURSE]
You okay, ma'am?

00:17:52.894 --> 00:17:54.196
[WOMAN]
I'm sorry.

00:17:54.296 --> 00:17:56.267
I think I might need
a wheelchair, too.

00:17:56.367 --> 00:17:59.607
Mrs. Goda? Are you ready to go?

00:17:59.708 --> 00:18:02.981
Oh, please, go ahead and take
the woman next to me first.

00:18:03.081 --> 00:18:05.820
It's her first, and
she's a little scared.

00:18:05.920 --> 00:18:07.356
Oh! Yes, but...

00:18:07.456 --> 00:18:09.159
Are you sure?
You gonna be all right?

00:18:09.259 --> 00:18:10.730
I'm fine.

00:18:10.830 --> 00:18:12.432
(Yuriko gasps)

00:18:12.532 --> 00:18:16.608
Don't worry, Mom,
I got this.

00:18:16.708 --> 00:18:19.079
(Ladies gasp)
Go ahead.
I'll follow you.

00:18:19.179 --> 00:18:20.281
Uh-huh...

00:18:20.382 --> 00:18:22.185
[TAKEO]
It's going to be all right.

00:18:22.285 --> 00:18:24.624
Big Brother is going to get
you where you need to go.

00:18:24.724 --> 00:18:29.233
And then you'll
get to meet my best friend Suna
and my girlfriend Ms. Yamato!

00:18:29.333 --> 00:18:31.938
[TAKEO]
They're good people.
You'll like 'em.

00:18:32.039 --> 00:18:33.609
And you'll meet
Mom and Dad, too!

00:18:33.709 --> 00:18:36.047
So just take it easy
and come on out!

00:18:36.147 --> 00:18:39.721
Hey, Mrs. Goda!
Thanks to you, the baby was
born without any problems.

00:18:39.821 --> 00:18:42.760
Now it's your turn!
Good luck in there!

00:18:42.860 --> 00:18:44.063
Thanks a lot!

00:18:44.163 --> 00:18:45.566
Maybe the two of our kids

00:18:45.666 --> 00:18:47.469
will end up being friends
with each other.

00:18:47.570 --> 00:18:51.912
[TAKEO]
You hear that? You've got a
friend waiting for you too!

00:18:54.784 --> 00:18:55.920
Um, right this way.

00:18:56.020 --> 00:18:57.422
[YURIKO]
Just hold on
just a second.

00:18:57.522 --> 00:19:00.596
Take, where's my
black bag? I need it.

00:19:00.696 --> 00:19:02.667
Got it!

00:19:02.767 --> 00:19:03.736
Ahh!
Here ya go, Mom.

00:19:03.836 --> 00:19:05.806
Yes, yes. Thanks, hon.

00:19:09.113 --> 00:19:10.415
Oh!

00:19:10.515 --> 00:19:12.185
Okay, time to have a baby.

00:19:12.285 --> 00:19:14.791
Ready, nurse? Try'n keep up!

00:19:14.891 --> 00:19:17.329
(Doors close)

00:19:19.299 --> 00:19:21.537
[TAKEO]
Thanks, guys.

00:19:21.638 --> 00:19:23.341
[SUNA]
All we can do now is wait.

00:19:23.441 --> 00:19:25.211
[TAKEO]
Yeah.

00:19:29.153 --> 00:19:31.090
(Baby cries)
(All gasp)

00:19:31.190 --> 00:19:33.361
[DOCTOR]
Congratulations,
Mrs. Goda!

00:19:33.461 --> 00:19:35.733
Everything went fine!

00:19:35.833 --> 00:19:39.173
And healthy, too!
Nine pounds and four ounces.

00:19:39.273 --> 00:19:41.243
(Rinko squealing)
Thank you so much!

00:19:41.343 --> 00:19:43.882
Mr. Goda, your wife
did wonderfully!

00:19:43.982 --> 00:19:45.452
Thank you so much!

00:19:45.553 --> 00:19:48.892
Congratulations! You're the
father of a happy baby girl!

00:19:48.992 --> 00:19:50.563
Thank you so much!

00:19:50.663 --> 00:19:52.532
<i>Oh my God!</i>

00:19:52.633 --> 00:19:57.242
<i>This is so amazing.</i>
<i>She did so great.</i>

00:19:57.342 --> 00:20:00.916
<i>Over nine pounds</i>
<i>of so great!</i>

00:20:01.016 --> 00:20:03.287
She's absolutely
adorable!

00:20:03.387 --> 00:20:04.991
She's so small.

00:20:05.091 --> 00:20:06.460
Yeah, I dunno about that.

00:20:06.561 --> 00:20:08.397
She's twice as big
as all the others.

00:20:08.498 --> 00:20:10.803
[RINKO]
This is the first time
I've ever seen a baby

00:20:10.903 --> 00:20:12.707
right after it's been born!

00:20:12.807 --> 00:20:13.976
She's beautiful.

00:20:14.076 --> 00:20:16.380
Hmm...

00:20:16.480 --> 00:20:19.186
I'll be okay with it
if you two get married.

00:20:19.286 --> 00:20:20.790
No thanks.

00:20:20.890 --> 00:20:23.261
[TAKEO]
<i>I was born healthier</i>
<i>than most.</i>

00:20:23.361 --> 00:20:26.868
<i>And I grew up to be</i>
<i>bigger than most.</i>

00:20:26.968 --> 00:20:30.041
Ms. Yamato, one of these days

00:20:30.141 --> 00:20:33.882
I want to work at a job where
I can help other people.

00:20:34.751 --> 00:20:36.287
Yeah.

00:20:38.692 --> 00:20:43.936
I never thought that one
day Take would carry me
around like a princess...

00:20:44.036 --> 00:20:46.641
I've always thought of him
as my little bitty baby,

00:20:46.741 --> 00:20:50.281
but I guess he's finally
growing up now, isn't he?

00:20:50.381 --> 00:20:54.456
Yes, he is. And now we get
to do it all over again.

00:20:54.557 --> 00:20:57.529
Oh, what do you think
we should name her?

00:20:57.630 --> 00:21:02.539
[RINKO]
Your sister is so cute.
Super-duper cute!

00:21:02.640 --> 00:21:07.249
(Squeal)
She's so tiny!
And so warm and so soft!

00:21:07.349 --> 00:21:09.086
Oh, and those finger nails!
She's so squishy!

00:21:09.186 --> 00:21:11.958
[TAKEO]
<i>Seeing her hold a baby</i>
<i>is so precious...</i>

00:21:12.058 --> 00:21:13.729
<i>I love her!</i>

00:21:13.829 --> 00:21:18.504
I think I want to work
in a nursery school or
maybe become a midwife.

00:21:18.605 --> 00:21:20.241
That sounds perfect!

00:21:20.341 --> 00:21:23.514
Actually, those would be
two completely different
degrees in college.

00:21:23.615 --> 00:21:26.955
Ah!
Can you cut it out with
the smart talk for once?

00:21:27.055 --> 00:21:30.094
[RINKO]
I wonder what your little sister
will end up calling you.

00:21:30.195 --> 00:21:33.201
Maybe "Big Brother." Or "Bro."

00:21:33.301 --> 00:21:35.806
[TAKEO]
Oh yeah. "Bro."
I like that!

00:21:35.906 --> 00:21:38.779
[SUNA]
I'm betting it'll just
be "Takeo" because, well,

00:21:38.879 --> 00:21:39.948
that's your name.

00:21:40.048 --> 00:21:42.920
[TAKEO]
"Takeo," huh? Cool.

00:21:43.020 --> 00:21:44.724
I can live with that.

00:21:44.824 --> 00:21:47.062
♪Closing song♪

00:22:54.429 --> 00:22:57.670
[TAKEO]
Next episode:
My Chocolate.

